  <file id="954" original="/csunplugged/topics/content/en/error-detection-and-correction/programming-challenges/detect-parity-error-in-six-rows/scratch-hints.md" source-language="en" target-language="en-UD" datatype="plaintext">
    <body>
      <trans-unit id="10528" identifier="d9d5697fb82b951021d3e19c3939ffee">
        <source>Make a variable called “black cards total” and set its value to 0.</source>
        <target>crwdns10528:0crwdne10528:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10529" identifier="51c7b82feec2e76d12fb778507efcd65">
        <source>Make a string variable called “row” and set its value to the input entered
by the end user.</source>
        <target>crwdns10529:0crwdne10529:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10530" identifier="4794e518692f6c1636a9a0773e3d0b1c">
        <source>Check each letter of the string and if it’s ‘B’ add 1 to the “black cards
total”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10530:0crwdne10530:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10531" identifier="a46cd13cc4c5d5ba4c2a8126c5333b3c">
        <source>If the value of the “black cards total” is even (after checking every card
in the row), display a message that the parity row is ok.</source>
        <target>crwdns10531:0crwdne10531:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10532" identifier="6c3f8a6c9cde5f45b507cb1b8956c00c">
        <source>If the value of the “black cards total” is odd, display a message that
the row has a parity error.</source>
        <target>crwdns10532:0crwdne10532:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10533" identifier="aa2a0c615745313d92507e4dceb7cc21">
        <source>Repeat this 6 times (for each row).</source>
        <target>crwdns10533:0crwdne10533:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10534" identifier="f33d46db20b024d4b72d2e7e3943f53d">
        <source>You can access a letter at the specified position in a string by using
the &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (1) of [world]&lt;/code&gt; block under “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10534:0[world]crwdne10534:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10535" identifier="b3f38b5bce22059c78a7498b774ea904">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:letter (1) of [world] //w&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10535:0[world]crwdne10535:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[2]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10536" identifier="f05bc4fbd37b9a919535e0bfacb00f76">
        <source>In this challenge you need to access all the letters in user’s input
(each row of the parity trick) and check to see how many of them
are equal to B (black).</source>
        <target>crwdns10536:0crwdne10536:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10537" identifier="919f1cfeadc417110703fa378b505c8a">
        <source>Store the total number of black squares in a variable called “black
cards total”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10537:0crwdne10537:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[3]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10538" identifier="4c8b5356652b84eab1850e4166a0d5fa">
        <source>You can find how many letters a string has by using the
&lt;code&gt;scratch:length of [world]&lt;/code&gt; block unders “Operators”.</source>
        <target>crwdns10538:0[world]crwdne10538:0</target>
        <note>Context: Paragraph text&#13;
XPath: /ul/li[4]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10539" identifier="74b149e3b36f1e579074bdc00ee459a7">
        <source>To find out if a number is even or odd, use the &lt;code&gt;scratch:() mod ()&lt;/code&gt; block
(under &quot;Operators&quot;) to find the remainder after dividing that number by
two.</source>
        <target>crwdns10539:0crwdne10539:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[5]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10540" identifier="2f8afc38cafe1c4e222387f03bd8cafe">
        <source>If the remainder is zero the number is even.</source>
        <target>crwdns10540:0crwdne10540:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[5]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
      <trans-unit id="10541" identifier="93f1d0c9d19c520c234d5439590b9ffa">
        <source>For example: &lt;code&gt;scratch:(37) mod (10) //7&lt;/code&gt;</source>
        <target>crwdns10541:0crwdne10541:0</target>
        <note>Context: XPath: /ul/li[5]/p</note>
      </trans-unit>
